sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates a new function.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Location - Name of the location.
  • Name - Name of the function.
  • Memory Allocated - Amount of memory in MB available for a function.
  • Runtime - Runtime in which to run the function.
  • Service Account Email - The email of the function's service account.
  • Source Archive URL - Google Cloud Storage URL, starting with gs://, pointing to the zip archive which contains the function.
  • Timeout - Function execution timeout.
  • Entry Point - Name of the function (as defined in source code) that will be executed.
  • Max Instances - Limit on the maximum number of function instances that may coexist at a given time.
  • Ingress Settings - Ingress settings for the function.
  • VPC Connector - Name of the VPC Network Connector.
  • VPC Connector EgressSettings - The egress settings for the connector.
  • Labels - Labels is on object containing Key and Value.
  • Environment Variables - Environment Variables is on object containing Name and Value.

Outputs:

  • Function - Object containing Operation ID , Metadata, Type, Target, Request, Type, Name, Source Archive URL, Entry Point, Timeout, Available Memory MB, Service Account Email, Runtime, and VPC Connector.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Cloud Functions, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid Project ID.
  • Invalid Location.
  • Function exist.
  • Invalid service account email.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Cloud Functions connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Cloud Functions Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_hub_action_type_definition"><sys_hub_action_type_definition action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><access>public</access><acls/><action_template/><active>true</active><annotation/><callable_by_client_api>false</callable_by_client_api><category display_value="Function Management">e392e41c1b9dd41015dfdce7cc4bcb87</category><copied_from>43991c5d1bdd581015dfdce7cc4bcb41</copied_from><copied_from_name>Create Function For Http</copied_from_name><description><p>Creates a new function.</p>
<p><b>Inputs:</p></b>
<ul>
<li><b>Project ID</b> - Unique ID of the project.</li>
<li><b>Location</b> - Name of the location.</li>
<li><b>Name</b> - Name of the function.</li>
<li><b>Memory Allocated</b> - Amount of memory in MB available for a function. </li>
<li><b>Runtime</b> - Runtime in which to run the function.</li>
<li><b>Service Account Email</b> - The email of the function's service account.</li>
<li><b>Source Archive URL</b> - Google Cloud Storage URL, starting with gs://, pointing to the zip archive which contains the function.</li>
<li><b>Timeout</b> - Function execution timeout.</li>
<li><b>Entry Point</b> - Name of the function (as defined in source code) that will be executed.</li>
<li><b>Max Instances</b> - Limit on the maximum number of function instances that may coexist at a given time.</li>
<li><b>Ingress Settings</b> -  Ingress settings for the function.</li>
<li><b>VPC Connector</b> - Name of the VPC Network Connector.</li>
<li><b>VPC Connector EgressSettings</b> - The egress settings for the connector.</li>
<li><b>Labels</b> - Labels is on object containing Key and Value.</li>
<li><b>Environment Variables</b> - Environment Variables is on object containing Name and Value.</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Outputs:</p></b>
<ul>
<li><b>Function</b> - Object containing Operation ID
, Metadata, Type, Target, Request, Type, Name, Source Archive URL, Entry Point, Timeout, Available Memory MB, Service Account Email, Runtime, and VPC Connector.</li>
<li><b>Status</b> - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Cloud Functions, Status is set to “Error".</li>
<li><b>Error Message</b> - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.
</li>
</ul>

<p><b>Error Messages:</p></b>
<ul>
<li>Invalid Project ID.</li>
<li>Invalid Location.</li>
<li>Function exist.</li>
<li>Invalid service account email.</li>
<li>Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.</li>
</ul>

<p> To use this action, a corresponding Google Cloud Functions connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Cloud Functions Connection & Credential alias.  <a target="_blank" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/search?q=Create+a+Connection+%26+Credential+alias">Learn More</a></p>

<p><b>Note</b>: Requires a subscription for production use. <a target="_blank" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context=CSHelp:IntegrationHub-licensing-information">Read     var payload = {
        "name": "projects/" + inputs.projectid + "/locations/" + inputs.location + "/functions/" + inputs.name,
        "sourceArchiveUrl": "gs://" + inputs.sourceArchiveUrl,
        "httpsTrigger": {},
        "entryPoint": inputs.entryPoint,
        "timeout": inputs.timeout + "s",
        "availableMemoryMb": inputs.availableMemoryMb,
        "serviceAccountEmail": inputs.serviceAccountEmail,
        "runtime": inputs.runtime,
        "ingressSettings": "ALLOW_ALL"
    }
    if (inputs.ingressSettings)
        payload.ingressSettings = inputs.ingressSettings;
    if (inputs.vpcConnector)
        payload.vpcConnector = inputs.vpcConnector;
    if (inputs.vpcConnectorEgressSettings)
        payload.vpcConnectorEgressSettings = inputs.vpcConnectorEgressSettings;
    if (inputs.maxInstances)
       payload.maxInstances = inputs.maxInstances;
    if (inputs.labels.length > 0) {
        var labels = {};
        inputs.labels.forEach(function(label) {
            if (label.key.trim() && label.value.trim())
                labels[label.key.trim()] =label.value.trim();
        });
        payload['labels'] = labels;
    }
    if (inputs.environmentVariables.length > 0) {
        var enVariables = {};
        inputs.environmentVariables.forEach(function(eVariable) {
            if (eVariable.name.trim() && eVariable.value.trim()){
               enVariables[eVariable.name.trim().toString()] = eVariable.value.trim().toString();
            }
        });
        payload['environmentVariables'] = enVariables;
    }
    outputs.location = inputs.location;
    outputs.projectid = inputs.projectid;
    outputs.payload = JSON.stringify(payload);
})(inputs, outputs);</value><variable display_value="">71aa7f6647032200b4fad7527c9a719b</variable></sys_variable_value><sys_element_mapping action="delete_multiple"
